main event: A bright spot-shaped light object was observed moving laterally in a northerly direction and disappearing over trees in Reynoldsville, Pennsylvania on June 29, 1963.
interesting points: The object appeared as a bright spot-shaped light, believed to be over a mile away.
The object moved laterally in a northerly direction and disappeared over trees in the northeast direction.
Another sighting was reported on June 23, 1963 of a shepherd egg-shaped object at treetop level, hovering and glowing white in color, before heading north.
The report includes a handwritten letter describing the June 23rd sighting.
The report concludes the June 29th sighting was likely a balloon or aircraft, but states there was insufficient data to definitively evaluate the sighting.
sighted object: bright spot-shaped light, shepherd egg-shaped object
